    title: "Oxygen Delivery Systems",
    cellular: "Oxygen delivery systems are classified as low-flow (variable FiO2) and high-flow (fixed FiO2). Low-flow devices: nasal cannula (1-6 L/min, 24-44% FiO2, increases 4% per liter), simple face mask (5-10 L/min, 40-60%), partial rebreather (6-10 L/min, 60-80%), non-rebreather (10-15 L/min, 80-95%). High-flow devices: Venturi mask (specific FiO2 selection 24-50%), high-flow nasal cannula (HFNC, 20-60 L/min, 21-100% FiO2, provides PEEP-like effect). HFNC benefits include humidification, dead space washout, and improved mucociliary clearance. Device selection based on clinical need, FiO2 requirement, and patient tolerance.",
