    title: "Mechanical Ventilation Fundamentals",
    cellular: "Mechanical ventilation supports or replaces spontaneous breathing. Indications: respiratory failure (PaO2 below 60 on supplemental O2 or PaCO2 above 50 with acidosis), airway protection, anticipated deterioration. Modes: volume-control (set tidal volume, variable pressure), pressure-control (set pressure, variable volume), and pressure support (augments spontaneous breaths). Initial settings: tidal volume 6-8 mL/kg ideal body weight (lung-protective), rate 12-16, PEEP 5-8 cmH2O, FiO2 100% initially then wean to lowest maintaining SpO2 92-96%. Monitoring: peak and plateau pressures, auto-PEEP, respiratory mechanics, and patient-ventilator synchrony. Lung-protective ventilation (ARDSNet): Vt 6 mL/kg IBW, plateau pressure below 30 cmH2O.",
