    cellular: "Advanced ventilator modes address specific clinical needs. SIMV (Synchronized Intermittent Mandatory Ventilation): set rate with spontaneous breaths between mandatory breaths, used for weaning. PRVC (Pressure-Regulated Volume Control): guarantees tidal volume using lowest needed pressure. APRV (Airway Pressure Release Ventilation): prolonged high CPAP with brief release periods, improves oxygenation in ARDS. BiLevel/BiPAP (ventilator mode): alternating between high and low pressure levels. Proportional assist ventilation: adjusts support based on patient effort. NAVA (Neurally Adjusted Ventilatory Assist): uses diaphragmatic electrical activity to trigger and size breaths. Mode selection depends on clinical scenario, patient pathology, and institutional expertise.",
