    cellular: "Acute respiratory distress syndrome is defined by the Berlin criteria: acute onset, bilateral opacities not fully explained by effusions/atelectasis, respiratory failure not fully explained by cardiac failure, PaO2/FiO2 ratio classification (mild 200-300, moderate 100-200, severe below 100). Lung-protective ventilation (ARDSNet protocol): Vt 4-8 mL/kg IBW (target 6), plateau pressure below 30 cmH2O, PEEP per FiO2/PEEP table. Prone positioning for moderate-severe ARDS (P/F below 150): 16+ hours per day, reduces mortality by 16%. Additional strategies: neuromuscular blockade in first 48 hours for severe ARDS, conservative fluid management, and ECMO for refractory cases. Recruitment maneuvers may be considered but evidence is mixed.",
