    cellular: "Asthma is characterized by reversible airway obstruction, bronchial hyperresponsiveness, and inflammation. Acute management by severity: mild-moderate (SABA q20min x3, consider ipratropium, oral corticosteroids), severe (continuous nebulization, IV magnesium sulfate 2g, subcutaneous terbutaline or epinephrine), and near-fatal (intubation with ketamine sedation, permissive hypercapnia, slow respiratory rate). Status asthmaticus is severe asthma unresponsive to initial treatment. Intubation considerations: risk of dynamic hyperinflation and auto-PEEP, use low rate/low Vt strategy with prolonged expiratory time. Heliox (helium-oxygen mixture) may improve gas distribution in severe obstruction. Peak flow monitoring guides treatment response and disposition.",
